OL,3,CSchool-run driver had 'tunnel vision'
OL,4,Cbefore hitting teen, inquest told
OL,6,FIn a statement, a road safety expert
OL,7,Fsaid there was no safe place where Mr
OL,8,FBrooke could have stopped after he
OL,9,Fstarted to feel unwell and by the time
OL,10,Fhe had passed some traffic lights.
OL,12,FThe inquest heard that Mr Brooke's
OL,13,Fmedical history included an episode
OL,14,Fwhere he fainted in 1985, and a dizzy
OL,15,Fspell in 2009 when he had been
OL,16,Fdiagnosed with pneumonia. The 2009
OL,17,Fincident had been recorded by his GP
OL,18,Fas "fainting" but Mr Brooke said he
OL,19,Fhad not fainted.
